article.headline: Georgetown 70, Stetson 50
article.story: WASHINGTON (AP) -- Roy Hibbert had 17 points and 10 rebounds and Georgetown scored the first 15 points of a 70-50 victory over winless Stetson on Saturday night. The Hoyas (5-2) took the game over in the opening minutes, going inside to the 7-foot-2 Hibbert early and often against the overmatched Hatters. Hibbert and guard Jonathan Wallace, who hit two 3-pointers, combined for all the points in the Hoyas' opening run that ended when Will Holloman scored on a three-point play 5 minutes into the game. The Hoyas led by as many as 27 points in the first half and were up 45-20 at halftime. Hibbert finished the opening half with 13 points and nine rebounds. Brandon Bowman and Marc Eggerson each added 12 points for the Hoyas. Anthony Register led the Hatters (0-8) with 17 points. The Hispanic College Fund Basketball Classic was played in McDonough Arena, Georgetown's on-campus facility, and drew a crowd of 2,146.
